Using finite element model (Equation (13)), Equation (11b) after summing over entire element can also be written as in global form:
(16)Π2=∑e=1NEΠ2(e)=∑e=1NE{Λ}T(e)[Kf](e){Λ}(e)=12{q}T[Kf]{q}
where, [Kf] is the global foundation stiffness matrix.

Using finite element model (Equation (13)), Equation (12) after summing over entire element can also be written as in global form:
(17)Π3=∑e=1NEΠ3(e)=12∑e=1NE{Λ}T(e)λ[Kg](e){Λ}(e)dA=12{q}Tλ[Kg]{q}
where, λ and [Kg] are defined as the hygrothermal buckling load parameters and the global geometric stiffness matrix, respectively.

Equation (19) can be rewritten as:
(20)[K]{q}=λ[Kg]{q}
where [K]=[Kb]+[Ks]+[Kf] with [Kb],[Ks],[Kf] and [Kg] are defined in the Appendix.

